{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/setting-up-a-brand-new-mac-for-development/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I have to set up a MacBook Pro fairly often - when starting a new job and when buying a new personal computer. I created this article back in 2015 when I got my first Mac and have been updating it ever since with whatever I need as my job evolves. I'm primarily a full-stack web developer, so most of my needs will revolve around JavaScript/Node.js.</p>\n<h2 id=\"getting-started\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#getting-started\" aria-label=\"getting started permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting Started</h2>\n<p>The setup assistant will launch once you turn the computer on. Enter your language, time zone, Apple ID, and so on. The first thing you should do is update macOS to get the latest security updates and patches.</p>\n<h2 id=\"homebrew\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#homebrew\" aria-label=\"homebrew permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Homebrew</h2>\n<p>Install the <a href=\"https://brew.sh/\">Homebrew</a> package manager. This will allow you to install almost any app from the command line.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">/usr/bin/ruby -e <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Install <a href=\"https://sourabhbajaj.com/mac-setup/Homebrew/Cask.html\">Homebrew Cask</a> for GUI applications.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">brew tap caskroom/cask</code></pre></div>\n<p>Make sure everything is up to date.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">brew update</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"install-apps\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-apps\" aria-label=\"install apps permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install Apps</h2>\n<p>Here are some the programs I always install.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Don't install Node.js through Homebrew. Use nvm (below).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Program</th>\n<th>Purpose</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">Visual Studio Code</a></td>\n<td>text editor</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.google.com/chrome/\">Google Chrome</a></td>\n<td>web browser</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/products/\">Firefox</a></td>\n<td>web browser</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://www.opera.com/\">Opera</a></td>\n<td>web browser</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.spectacleapp.com/\">Spectacle</a></td>\n<td>window resizing</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://iterm2.com/\">iTerm2</a></td>\n<td>terminal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://www.docker.com/\">Docker</a></td>\n<td>development</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"http://www.videolan.org/vlc/index.html\">VLC Media Player</a></td>\n<td>media player</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Core</span>\nbrew <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">git</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">make</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  travis\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Cask</span>\nbrew cask <span class=\"token function\">install</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  visual-studio-code <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  google-chrome <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  firefox <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  opera <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  spectacle <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  iterm2 <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  docker <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span>\n  vlc</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"shell\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#shell\" aria-label=\"shell permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Shell</h2>\n<p>Catalina comes with <a href=\"http://zsh.sourceforge.net/\">zsh</a> as the default shell. Install <a href=\"https://ohmyz.sh/\">Oh My Zsh</a> for sensible defaults.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">sh</span> -c <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -fsSL https://raw.github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/master/tools/install.sh<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"nodejs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nodejs\" aria-label=\"nodejs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Node.js</h2>\n<p>Use <a href=\"https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm/blob/master/README.md\">Node Version Manager (nvm)</a> to install Node.js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.35.2/install.sh <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">bash</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"install\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install\" aria-label=\"install permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install</h3>\n<p>Install the latest version.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">nvm <span class=\"token function\">install</span> node</code></pre></div>\n<p>Restart terminal and run the final command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">nvm use node</code></pre></div>\n<p>Confirm that you are using the latest version of Node and npm.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">node -v\n<span class=\"token function\">npm</span> -v</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"update\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#update\" aria-label=\"update permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Update</h3>\n<p>For later, here's how to update nvm.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">nvm <span class=\"token function\">install</span> node --reinstall-packages-from<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>node</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"change-version\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#change-version\" aria-label=\"change version permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Change version</h3>\n<p>Here's how to switch to another version and use it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">nvm install xx.xx\nnvm use xx.xx</code></pre></div>\n<p>And to set the default:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">nvm alias default xx.xx</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"git\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#git\" aria-label=\"git permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Git</h2>\n<p>The first thing you should do with Git is <a href=\"https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup\">set your global configuration</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">touch</span> ~/.gitconfig</code></pre></div>\n<p>Input your name, email, GitHub username, some aliases, and connect Git to the OS X Keychain.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>user<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  name   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> Firstname Lastname\n  email  <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> you@example.com\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>github<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  user   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> username\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>alias<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n  a      <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">add</span>\n  ca     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> commit -a\n  cam    <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> commit -am\n  cm     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> commit -m\n  s      <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> status\n  pom    <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> push origin master\n  pog    <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> push origin gh-pages\n  puom   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pull origin master\n  puog   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> pull origin gh-pages\n  cob    <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> checkout -b\n  co     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> checkout\n  fp     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> fetch --prune --all\n  l      <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> log --oneline --decorate --graph\n  lall   <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> log --oneline --decorate --graph --all\n  <span class=\"token function\">ls</span>     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> log --oneline --decorate --graph --stat\n  lt     <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> log --graph --decorate --pretty<span class=\"token operator\">=</span>format:<span class=\"token string\">'%C(yellow)%h%Creset%C(auto)%d%Creset %s %Cgreen(%cr) %C(bold blue)%an%Creset'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>With the above aliases, I can run <code class=\"language-text\">git s</code> instead of <code class=\"language-text\">git status</code>, for example. The less I have to type repeatedly, the happier I am.</p>\n<h2 id=\"ssh\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ssh\" aria-label=\"ssh permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>SSH</h2>\n<p>Simplify the process of SSHing into other boxes. Create an SSH config file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> ~/.ssh <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">touch</span> ~/.ssh/config</code></pre></div>\n<p>Add the following contents, changing the variables for any hosts that you connect to. Using the below willbe the same as running <code class=\"language-text\">ssh -i ~/.ssh/key.pem user@example.com</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">Host *\n  AddKeysToAgent <span class=\"token function\">yes</span>\n  UseKeychain <span class=\"token function\">yes</span>\n  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa\n\nHost myssh\n  HostName example.com\n  User user\n  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/key.pem</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now just run the alias to connect.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">ssh</span> myssh</code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"generate-ssh-key\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#generate-ssh-key\" aria-label=\"generate ssh key permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Generate SSH key</h4>\n<p>You can <a href=\"https://help.github.com/articles/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent/\">generate an SSH key</a> to distribute.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">ssh-keygen -t rsa -b <span class=\"token number\">4096</span> -C <span class=\"token string\">\"email@example.com\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">ssh-add -K ~/.ssh/id_rsa</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"settings\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#settings\" aria-label=\"settings permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Settings</h2>\n<p>I don't like a lot of the Apple defaults so here are the things I always change.</p>\n<p>To get the Home folder in the finder, press <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + H</code> and drag the home folder to the sidebar.</p>\n<h3 id=\"general\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#general\" aria-label=\"general permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>General</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Dark mode</li>\n<li>Google Chrome default browser</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"dock\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dock\" aria-label=\"dock permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dock</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Automatically hide and show Dock</li>\n<li>Show indicators for open applications</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"keyboard\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#keyboard\" aria-label=\"keyboard permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Keyboard</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Key Repeat -> Fast</li>\n<li>Delay Until Repeat -> Short</li>\n<li>Disable \"Correct spelling automatically\"</li>\n<li>Disable \"Capitalize words automatically\"</li>\n<li>Disable \"Add period with double-space\"</li>\n<li>Disable \"Use smart quotes and dashes\"</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"security-and-privacy\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#security-and-privacy\" aria-label=\"security and privacy permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Security and Privacy</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Allow apps downloaded from App Store and identified developers</li>\n<li>Turn FileVault On (makes sure SSD is securely encrypted)</li>\n<li>Turn Firewall On (extra security measure)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"sharing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sharing\" aria-label=\"sharing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sharing</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Change computer name</li>\n<li>Make sure all file sharing is disabled</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"users--groups\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#users--groups\" aria-label=\"users  groups permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Users &#x26; Groups</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Add \"Spectacle\" to Login Items</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"defaults\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#defaults\" aria-label=\"defaults permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Defaults</h2>\n<p>A few more commands to change some defaults.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token comment\"># Show Library folder</span>\nchflags nohidden ~/Library\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Show hidden files</span>\ndefaults <span class=\"token function\">write</span> com.apple.finder AppleShowAllFiles YES\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Show path bar</span>\ndefaults <span class=\"token function\">write</span> com.apple.finder ShowPathbar -bool <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Show status bar</span>\ndefaults <span class=\"token function\">write</span> com.apple.finder ShowStatusBar -bool <span class=\"token boolean\">true</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># Prevent Two Finger Scroll on Chrome</span>\ndefaults <span class=\"token function\">write</span> com.google.Chrome AppleEnableSwipeNavigateWithScrolls -bool FALSE</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"application-settings\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#application-settings\" aria-label=\"application settings permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Application Settings</h2>\n<h3 id=\"chrome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#chrome\" aria-label=\"chrome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Chrome</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Turn off \"warn before quitting\"</li>\n<li>Install ublock origin</li>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/devtools-theme-new-moon/lndddploiofhfpdcoclegenegblkhlfk?hl=en\">DevTools Theme - New Moon</a></li>\n<li>\n<p>Settings</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Set theme to Dark</li>\n<li>Go to <code class=\"language-text\">chrome://flags</code> and set Developer Tools Experiments to Enabled</li>\n<li>Go to Experiments and select Allow custom UI themes</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"visual-studio-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#visual-studio-code\" aria-label=\"visual studio code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Visual Studio Code</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Press <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + P</code> and click Install code command in PATH.</li>\n<li>Install Prettier</li>\n<li>Install <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=taniarascia.new-moon-vscode\">New Moon Theme</a></li>\n<li>Install GitLens</li>\n<li>\n<p>Keyboard Shortcuts</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Copy Line Down - <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + E</code></li>\n<li>Delete Line - <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + D</code></li>\n<li>Reload Windw - Remove Development Mode from When</li>\n<li>Format Document - <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + L</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"spectacle\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#spectacle\" aria-label=\"spectacle permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Spectacle</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Full Screen: <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + SHIFT + &#39;</code> (prevents messing with other commands)</li>\n<li>Left Half: <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + OPTION + LEFT</code></li>\n<li>Right Half: <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + OPTION + RIGHT</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"iterm2\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#iterm2\" aria-label=\"iterm2 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>iTerm2</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://coderwall.com/p/h6yfda/use-and-to-jump-forwards-backwards-words-in-iterm-2-on-os-x\">Use ⌥ ← and ⌥→ to jump forwards / backwards</a></li>\n<li>Set tab to open in same location</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>That sums it up for my current preferences on setting up a MacBook Pro. I hope it helped speed up your process, or gave you ideas for the next time you're setting one up.</p>","timeToRead":7,"excerpt":"I have to set up a MacBook Pro fairly often - when starting a new job and when buying a new personal computer. I created this article back…","frontmatter":{"title":"macOS Catalina 10.15: Setting up a Brand New Mac for Development","thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":150,"height":150,"src":"/static/cb5559b72715b61014d79b2e4b990402/4148e/apple.png","srcSet":"/static/cb5559b72715b61014d79b2e4b990402/4148e/apple.png 1x"}}},"slug":"setting-up-a-brand-new-mac-for-development","date":"2020-02-17T00:00:00.000Z","categories":["Tools"],"tags":["apple","macos","setup"],"template":"post"},"fields":{"slug":"/setting-up-a-brand-new-mac-for-development/","date":"2020-02-17T00:00:00.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/setting-up-a-brand-new-mac-for-development/"}}}